Algorithm:

1. Start
2. Declare the varibale mychar of char type
3. Get the input manually form the user using printf & scanf
4. Print the ASCII value of that character 
5. return a null value
6. End

#include <stdio.h>
int main()
{
char ch; // variable declaration.
printf("Enter a character");
scanf("%c",&ch); // user input.
printf("The ascii value of the ch variable is : %d", ch);
return 0;
}
